format/mdbook.md
     1→# mdBook-specific features
     2→
     3→## Hiding code lines
     4→
     5→There is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6→
     7→For the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8→This prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9→
    10→[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11→
    12→```bash
    13→# fn main() {
    14→    let x = 5;
    15→    let y = 6;
    16→
    17→    println!("{}", x + y);
    18→# }
    19→```
    20→
    21→Will render as
    22→
    23→```rust
    24→# fn main() {
    25→    let x = 5;
    26→    let y = 6;
    27→
    28→    println!("{}", x + y);
    29→# }
    30→```
    31→
    32→When you tap or hover the mouse over the code block, there will be an eyeball icon (<i class="fa fa-eye"></i>) which will toggle the visibility of the hidden lines.
    33→
    34→By default, this only works for code examples that are annotated with `rust`.
    35→However, you can define custom prefixes for other languages by adding a new line-hiding prefix in your `book.toml` with the language name and prefix character(s):
    36→
    37→```toml
    38→[output.html.code.hidelines]
    39→python = "~"
    40→```
    41→
    42→The prefix will hide any lines that begin with the given prefix. With the python prefix shown above, this:
    43→
    44→```bash
    45→~hidden()
    46→nothidden():
    47→~    hidden()
    48→    ~hidden()
    49→    nothidden()
    50→```
    51→
    52→will render as
    53→
    54→```python
    55→~hidden()
    56→nothidden():
    57→~    hidden()
    58→    ~hidden()
    59→    nothidden()
    60→```
    61→
    62→This behavior can be overridden locally with a different prefix. This has the same effect as above:
    63→
    64→~~~markdown
    65→```python,hidelines=!!!
    66→!!!hidden()
    67→nothidden():
    68→!!!    hidden()
    69→    !!!hidden()
    70→    nothidden()
    71→```
    72→~~~
    73→
